    "### 1.6 Supervised Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "Supervised learning is a category of machine learning in which the algorithm is trained on **labelled data** — a dataset where every input observation `xᵢ` is paired with a known output label `yᵢ`. The algorithm learns to minimise the discrepancy between its predictions `ŷ` and the true labels `y`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Formally, we seek a function `f` such that  \n",
    "`ŷ = f(X; θ)` and `L(y, ŷ)` is minimised,  \n",
    "where `θ` are the model parameters and `L` is a loss function.\n",
    "\n",
    "Both regression and classification are supervised learning problems. They differ only in the nature of the target variable and the choice of loss function.\n",
    "\n",
